[
  {
    "lesson_id": "019",
    "trigger_word": "nomiĝi",
    "title": "LESSON 19: THE '-IĜ-' SUFFIX",
    "header_color": "green",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "The suffix -IĜ- means \"to become\" or \"to",
          "change into a different state of being.\"",
          "",
          "ADJECTIVE → VERB (to become):",
          "varma   → varmiĝi    = warm → to become warm",
          "riĉa    → riĉiĝi     = rich → to get rich",
          "malpura → malpuriĝi  = dirty → to get dirty",
          "",
          "NOUN → VERB (to turn into):",
          "glacio  → glaciiĝi   = ice → to freeze",
          "patro   → patriĝi    = father → become father",
          "",
          "COMMON USES:",
          "nomiĝi     = to be named (Mi nomiĝas...)",
          "fariĝi     = to become",
          "",
          "KEY: -IĜ- verbs are intransitive - the",
          "subject changes, without needing an object!"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Leciono dek naŭ"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "lesson_id": "020",
    "trigger_word": "klavaro",
    "title": "LESSON 20: THE '-AR-' SUFFIX",
    "header_color": "green",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "The suffix -AR- means \"a collection\" or",
          "\"group of.\" It creates collective nouns from",
          "individual items.",
          "",
          "CREATING GROUPS:",
          "arbo    → arbaro     = tree → forest",
          "homo    → homaro     = person → humanity",
          "vorto   → vortaro    = word → dictionary",
          "ilo     → ilaro      = tool → toolkit",
          "besto   → bestaro    = animal → fauna",
          "",
          "THE PATTERN:",
          "Take any individual thing, add -ar-, get",
          "a collection or group of those things!",
          "",
          "Mi havas grandan vortaron.",
          "(I have a large dictionary.)",
          "",
          "One suffix to collect them all!"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Leciono dudek"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "lesson_id": "021",
    "trigger_word": "citaĵo",
    "title": "LESSON 21: THE '-AĴ-' SUFFIX",
    "header_color": "green",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "The suffix -AĴ- creates concrete things from",
          "verbs and adjectives. If -i is the action,",
          "-aĵ- is the physical thing.",
          "",
          "FROM VERBS TO THINGS:",
          "manĝi   → manĝaĵo    = to eat → food",
          "trinki  → trinkaĵo   = to drink → beverage",
          "vesti   → vestaĵo    = to dress → clothing",
          "konstrui→ konstruaĵo = to build → building",
          "skribi  → skribaĵo   = to write → writing",
          "",
          "FROM ADJECTIVES:",
          "bela    → belaĵo     = beautiful → beauty",
          "dolĉa   → dolĉaĵo    = sweet → candy",
          "",
          "Think: -AĴ- makes abstract actions concrete!",
          "The thing that results from the action."
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Leciono dudek unu"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "lesson_id": "022",
    "trigger_word": "komputilo",
    "title": "LESSON 22: THE '-IL-' SUFFIX",
    "header_color": "green",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "The suffix -IL- creates tools or instruments",
          "from verbs. If -i is the action, -il- is the",
          "tool that performs that action.",
          "",
          "FROM VERBS TO TOOLS:",
          "tranĉi  → tranĉilo   = to cut → knife",
          "skribi  → skribilo   = to write → pen",
          "komputi → komputilo  = to compute → computer",
          "ludi    → ludilo     = to play → toy",
          "mezuri  → mezurilo   = to measure → ruler",
          "",
          "ANY ACTION → ITS TOOL:",
          "malfermi → malfermilo = to open → opener",
          "trinki   → trinkilo   = to drink → cup",
          "",
          "Remember: -IL- is the thing you use to do",
          "the action. Simple and systematic!"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Leciono dudek du"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "lesson_id": "023",
    "trigger_word": "retejo",
    "title": "LESSON 23: THE '-EJ-' SUFFIX",
    "header_color": "green",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "The suffix -EJ- means \"place for\" or",
          "\"location where something happens.\"",
          "",
          "FROM VERBS TO PLACES:",
          "lerni   → lernejo    = to learn → school",
          "loĝi    → loĝejo     = to live → dwelling",
          "labori  → laborejo   = to work → workplace",
          "kuiri   → kuirejo    = to cook → kitchen",
          "",
          "FROM NOUNS TO PLACES:",
          "kafo    → kafejo     = coffee → café",
          "libro   → librejo    = book → library",
          "pano    → panejo     = bread → bakery",
          "hundo   → hundejo    = dog → kennel",
          "",
          "THE PATTERN:",
          "Whatever happens or is found there,",
          "add -ej- to make it a location!",
          "",
          "Where do you lerni? At the lernejo!"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Leciono dudek tri"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
